    "comment": "CALVIN Franka Panda on the PlayTable (calvin_env / PyBullet, eval scene D), 30 Hz. Implemented by demos/benchmarks/envs/calvin (HUD sim bridge; episodes are subtasks of the official 1000 evaluation chains). This contract is the env's default 'relative' action branch \u2014 the canonical CALVIN policy interface (rel_actions: world-frame normalized tcp deltas + binary gripper). The env also exposes an 8-dim absolute branch (pos + xyzw quat + gripper; BENCH_CONTROL=absolute) matching the official X-VLA eval client; see envs/calvin/calvin_abs.json (one wire contract per control mode). State = 15-dim robot_obs split per quantity ('order' reassembles). No env-side normalization (dtype + stats/limits only); per-dim distribution stats would come from the (not downloaded) dataset."
